      "content_license": "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body": "<p>As mentioned in <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/40268446/junit-5-how-to-assert-an-exception-is-thrown/78838077#comment106433328_40268446\">the comment</a> by <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/1075613/user1075613\">user1075613</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>you might be interested to check AssertJ for checking exceptions at it is more flexible than JUnit5</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>and it also generates fitting error message. <a href=\"https://assertj.github.io/doc/#assertj-core-exception-assertions-assertThatThrownBy\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Example</a>:</p>\n<pre><code>  assertThatThrownBy(() -&gt; someMethod(param1, param2))\n        .isInstanceOf(NullPointerException.class);\n</code></pre>\n"
